      "content": "Early 20th century eugenicists primarily relied on pseudo-scientific theories to justify their claims of racial superiority. They often cited flawed studies and misinterpreted data to argue that certain racial groups possessed superior intelligence, moral character, and physical attributes. They claimed that these groups were more \"fit\" for society and should be encouraged to reproduce, while deeming others as \"inferior\" and in need of \"improvement\" through selective breeding or sterilization. They also drew upon Social Darwinist ideology, which posited that the strongest and most \"fit\" individuals would naturally rise to the top of the social hierarchy, thereby reinforcing their notion of a hierarchical racial order.",
