      "content": "Eugenicists often used anthropometric measurements, such as skull shape and size, to differentiate between racial groups. They would measure the length and width of the skull, as well as the shape of the cranium, to supposedly determine the level of intelligence and \"civilization\" of a particular group. They would also examine the shape of the nose, lips, and jaw to determine the level of \"moral character\" and \"racial purity\".\n\nFor example, they would compare the supposed \"narrow\" and \"refined\" skull shape of Northern Europeans to the supposedly \"wide\" and \"coarse\" skull shape of Africans and Asians. They would also examine the supposed differences in the shape of the nose and lips, with Northern Europeans having a supposedly \"more refined\" nose and lips, while Africans and Asians had a supposedly \"coarser\" nose and lips.\n\nRegarding moral character, eugenicists would often cite studies that supposedly linked certain traits, such as \"moral degeneracy\" or \"savage behavior\", to specific racial groups. For example, they would cite studies that supposedly showed that Africans were more prone to \"savage behavior\" or that Asians were more likely to engage in \"moral degeneracy\".",
